      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal doctrine that protects fundamental rights from government overreach, even if those actions follow proper legal procedure. It ensures that the government cannot infringe upon deeply rooted liberties, such as privacy or free expression, without a very strong justification. This concept has been vital in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringed upon personal autonomy and basic human dignity. Ultimately, it serves as a bulwark against legislative tyranny in the American system.",
